@startuml
title POST /api/v1/registration/accounts — LOCAL TEACHER/RESEARCHER (201 Created)
autonumber

actor Client
participant "register_account()\n_register_local()" as View
participant "StudentInvite\nRegisterSerializer" as Serializer
participant "password_strength\n_errors()" as PwdCheck
participant "validate_registration\n_code()" as Validate
participant "redeem_non_student\n_local_invite()" as Redeem
participant "create_user_from\n_payload()" as CreateUser
database Postgres

Client -> View: POST /registration/accounts\n{method: "LOCAL", code, firstName,\nlastName, email, password, confirmPassword}
View -> Serializer: is_valid(raise_exception=True)
Serializer --> View: validated data

View -> View: password == confirmPassword?
View -> PwdCheck: password_strength_errors(password)
PwdCheck --> View: [] (no errors)

View -> Validate: validate_registration_code(code)
Validate -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ?
Postgres --> Validate: RegistrationCode (TEACHER type)
Validate --> View: RegistrationCode

note over View: code_type == TEACHER\n-> non-student registration path

== @transaction.atomic ==

View -> Redeem: redeem_non_student_local_invite(data)
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ?\nFOR UPDATE
Postgres --> Redeem: RegistrationCode (locked)
Redeem -> Redeem: validate code_type != STUDENT

Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE username = email OR email = email
Postgres --> Redeem: False (email not taken)

Redeem -> Redeem: generate_managed_username()
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE username = ?
Postgres --> Redeem: False (unique)

Redeem -> Redeem: _role_from_registration_code_type()\nTEACHER -> Role.TEACHER

Redeem -> CreateUser: create_user_from_payload(\nrole=TEACHER, creator=None)
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO app_users
Postgres --> CreateUser: User
CreateUser -> Postgres: DELETE FROM user_roles WHERE user_id = ?
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO user_roles\n(user_id, role=TEACHER)
CreateUser -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS teacher_profiles\nWHERE user_id = ?
Postgres --> CreateUser: False
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO teacher_profiles\n(user_id)
CreateUser --> Redeem: User

Redeem -> Postgres: UPDATE registration_codes\nSET times_used += 1
Redeem --> View: User

== end transaction ==

View -> View: RefreshToken.for_user(user)\ngenerate JWT tokens
View -> View: build_user_response(user, tokens)

View --> Client: 201 Created\n{message, username, name, email,\naccessToken, refreshToken,\nrole: ROLE_TEACHER, courseId: null}
@enduml
